<h1>CS-Visualizer Plugin Privacy Policy</h1>

<p><strong>Last Updated: March 31, 2026</strong></p>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>The CS-Visualizer Plugin is a companion tool for the CS-Visualizer webapp. We are committed to protecting your privacy.</p>

<h2>Data Collection</h2>
<p>The Plugin does NOT collect, store, or transmit personal data. Specifically:</p>
<ul>
<li>Your code and data are processed locally and never sent to external servers</li>
<li>No usage analytics or telemetry are collected</li>
<li>No account or registration is required to use the Plugin</li>
<li>Plugin settings are stored locally on your device only</li>
</ul>

<h2>Communication with CS-Visualizer</h2>
<p>The Plugin may communicate with the CS-Visualizer webapp to:</p>
<ul>
<li>Authenticate your account (if using a CS-Visualizer account)</li>
<li>Sync settings and preferences</li>
<li>Deliver features and updates</li>
</ul>
<p>Any data sent to CS-Visualizer servers is subject to the CS-Visualizer webapp's Privacy Policy.</p>

<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
<p>The Plugin does not integrate with any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking services.</p>

<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
<p>The Plugin does not knowingly collect information from children under 13. As no personal data is collected from any user, this Plugin is safe for all ages.</p>

<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this privacy policy at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date. Continued use of the Plugin means you accept the updated policy.</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>Questions about privacy? Contact us at davidfruc@gmail.com or visit the CS-Visualizer project repository.</p>

